.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH info 1  "info " 
.SH NAME
info \- Check whether a dialog is currently open
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBinfo\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Check whether a JavaScript dialog (alert, confirm, prompt, or beforeunload) is currently open. Returns JSON with the dialog\*(Aqs type, message, and default prompt text if applicable. Returns {"open": false} when no dialog is present.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  # Check for open dialog
  agentchrome dialog info
.SH CAPABILITIES
.PP
Browser dialog handling (alert, confirm, prompt, beforeunload)
.TP
.B dialog handle
Accept or dismiss the current browser dialog
.TP
.B action
Action to take: accept or dismiss
.TP
.B --text
Response text for prompt dialogs (only used with 'accept' action)
.TP
.B dialog info
Check whether a dialog is currently open
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Examples:
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog info\`
Check if a dialog is currently open
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle accept\`
Accept an alert or confirm dialog
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle dismiss\`
Dismiss a dialog
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle accept --text "my input"\`
Accept a prompt dialog with text
